cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of accurately localizing proteins in fluorescence microscopy images using a deep learning approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end neural network architecture for protein localization, which involves training the network on large amounts of data. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of experimental results on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
